Merge pull request #124 from verseles/refactor-sort-models-15132758881095053786

Refactor sortModels for performance and clarity

refactor: optimize sortModels by extracting value retrieval logic

Extracts the value retrieval logic in `sortModels` to a helper function defined outside the sort comparison callback. This reduces overhead by avoiding repetitive switch statement evaluation during sorting (O(N log N) -> O(1) for logic selection).

Logic remains semantically equivalent, preserving null handling and sorting direction.

Merge pull request #119 from verseles/optimize-ranking-memoization-2645139544826211164

Optimize ranking calculation with memoization

Optimize ranking calculation with memoization

This change introduces an `imputationCache` to `imputeMissingScores` in `src/lib/ranking.ts`.
This avoids redundant calculations when models have `superior_of` relationships, as the recursive calls can now reuse previously computed imputed models.
This transforms potentially exponential complexity in deep dependency chains into linear complexity.

- Added `imputationCache` optional parameter to `imputeMissingScores`
- Updated `rankModels` to create and pass this cache
- Added unit test in `src/lib/ranking.test.ts` to verify caching behavior
